text: I wonder what suburban women think.
author: sppeoples

text:
Trump's continued attack on McCain, seven months after his death, is not going over well among NH Republicans. 
https://apnews.com/59d2395c7af14261aaf0b023aec4c3b6 …
author: sppeoples

text: NH GOP Gov. Chris Sununu: “The media and certain folks don’t like how he says things and whatnot. And I agree with that... I’m a big believer that sometimes how you say something is just as important as what you say. It is a very different style and we don’t mesh with our styles”
author: sppeoples

text:
Republican National Committee member Steve Duprey: “President Donald Trump isn’t worthy to carry even John McCain’s navy cap. In no measure is he the patriot or public servant that John McCain was. Ever.”

Duprey refused to say whether he would vote for Trump in 2020.
author: sppeoples

text: In sharp contrast to Republicans in other states, some New Hampshire GOP leaders are actively encouraging — or at least failing to discourage — Trump primary challengers. @HunterMw and I break it down. https://apnews.com/59d2395c7af14261aaf0b023aec4c3b6 …
author: sppeoples

text: I know this debate will never be resolved, but I’d like a @GlobeTrotScott ruling on this. I’d like to do the right thing, yet I struggle to understand how using the seat I purchase as intended is a bad thing.
author: sppeoples

text: As a frequent traveler I’ve never understood this perspective. Shouldn’t you be angry at the airline for selling a cramped seat? Or yourself for not paying for more space? If I pay for a seat that reclines I’m going to recline.
author: sppeoples

text: Warren strategy: flood the zone in the early states: She has hired 65 staffers for IA, NH, SC and NV already. Since launching Dec. 31, she's held 26 events in the four states, including 11 separate town halls or house parties in Iowa and 10 in New Hampshire.
author: sppeoples

text: Elizabeth Warren, a longtime liberal superstar, is embracing an uncomfortable role in the crowded 2020 contest: the underdog. My story w @eschor and @HunterMw
author: sppeoples

text: Note that another former Romney adviser, Russ Schriefer, is now advising Maryland Gov. Larry Hogan, another potential Trump primary challenger.
author: sppeoples

text: Romney's office declined to comment: "We have no involvement in this."
author: sppeoples
